{"id":14882019,"mediaExerciseId":"1dc219f8-8d93-4d72-934f-05c1a2a8f49e","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"27","chapterTitle":"Leasing","groupId":612532,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":909,"solutions":[{"id":6504657,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"The goal of this task is to explain the appropriate discount rate to use in lease evaluation.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"In the decision-making process of borrowing versus leasing, one of the analyses that are performed is to calculate the interest rate that the company would have to pay in each scenario. \n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"But ***what type of loan is the leasing option compared to?***\n\nWe are taking as a reference the ***long-term loan alternative*** because it may be the one that best corresponds to the lease proposal in terms of time and therefore, it is more realistic for the analysis.\n\nFor this reason, the interest rate used for the comparison is the company's after-tax borrowing rate.\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"141e8fa8-ce87-491d-bcef-c3ca2ea68765","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSo